	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Regarding the worthiness of Pet heal spells, the following is lifted from an article (source www.stratics.com) that analyses efficient use of Mage pets for solo fighting.  The analysis deals with the level 8 heal, but the concept applies to all heals.<BR>
<BR>
***<BR>
<BR>
Healing your pet is a misunderstood set of tools. Players seem to apply measurements to the healing tools that lead them to ignore the heals in favor of burn spells. The measurements generally fall into one of three areas:<BR>
<BR>
1) Mana efficiency of a burn versus heal spell.<BR>
2) Single hit damage dealt by a mob versus heal points of heal spell.<BR>
3) Speed of a burn versus healing spell.<BR>
<BR>
These measurements do not capture the impact of the heal spell and ignore the main benefit of the heal spell, i.e., your pet now has extra rounds. If we shift to viewing damage over time, the heal spell does well as an alternative to a burn. A level 16 pet can hit for 20, bash for 8, double attack, and has a damage spell. There are various ways to arrange the numbers, but the pet should hit from 15 (partial hit) to 70 (full impact) in a round. With high agility pets, you can go several rounds without being hit. The damage over time for two rounds would be 30 to 140 and for three rounds would be 45 to 210. The heal spell in this range will heal about 40 or so. Given that the average mob in this range hits from 15 to 30, you can get a minimum of two rounds attacking and more than likely four to five rounds with one heal. <BR>
<BR>
Therefore, the heal spell creates roughly 30 to 210 damage for a cost of 25 mana points. A mob may hit for 20 points versus the 40 point heal however, a pet gets in several rounds and can inflict significantly more damage during retaliation. While a burn spell will bring a mob down faster; a heal uses less mana than multiple cast of high mana burns, cannot be resisted, and does not aggro the mob(s) on you.<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
